<br>
Iuldin 52nd Champion <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Daramin</span><br> <span class=usertitle>is too scared to Register</span><br>   <font color=#FF0000>(2/5/01 5:45:00 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   what I do is...</span><hr size=1> Use them to keep some of my warrior skills up. I have good 1hb/1hs/2hb, but I don't have good bash, so I dump skill points into bash when I have them. As a dualwielder I find raising bash to be difficult. Sure I ghetto-bash when I'm fighting casters, but otherwise I'm using kick. Can't wait to get kick/stun, but that's a long way away at level 30. :-)<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/usionx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sionx</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/21/01 3:21:05 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_exp.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: what I do is...</span><hr size=1> The comments here are good although I'd argue that Dual Wield and Dbl Atk progress quite well as long as you actually dual wield for about half of your XP each level.  I have been carrying 1HB and 1HS that can go in either slot so it's easier to get all 4 skills up each level.  (Note that your ATK rating is based on the weapon in your primary hand so carrying a PRIMARY only weapon will reduce your chances of getting them both maxed.<br>
<br>
I go to Crushbone (being a Wood Elf it's close to the trainer for those rare trips home) for skilling up Disarm.  Since you can gain skill points on green mobs it's easy to find Orcs with weapons which no-one will care about.  Also by the time you've hit lvl 35 to gain the skill, it can be fun to break up the trains that gather at the zone to GFay.  Newbies will love you for it too. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
